pageContext.claim: “And the CIA did not say affirmatively [the Saudi crown prince was involved with the death of Jamal Khashoggi] either, by the way. I'm not saying that they're saying he didn't do it, but they didn't say it affirmatively.”
pageContext.analysis: The Washington Post reported CIA concluded with "high confidence" that Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman ordered the assassination of journalist Jamal Khashoggi. This reporting was echoed by several lawmakers after being briefed by CIA Director Gina Haspel.
